abstract_summ: We collected total number of confirmed cases and deaths related to COVID-19 at the county level in the US from January 21, 2020 to April 23, 2020 . Multivariable linear mixed effects models were used to investigate potential correlations of health and demographic characteristics with the infection and mortality rates of the pandemic in US counties . Several factors, such as low education level and percentage of Black, were positively correlated with the death rate .
